---
Isa.  

O God! may I look up to Thee?  
		   I would address Thee if I may; 
 
		And this my one request should be, 
 
		      Teach me to pray.  
		Now, in my sorrow, I would ask, 
 
		   What thoughts to think, what words to say; 
 
		Prayer is a new and arduous task; 
 
		      Teach me to pray.
